<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1920&amp;p=17473#p17473"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Madara and Esper Dream 2; question about internal headers]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1920&amp;p=17473#p17473"><![CDATA[
Such headers used mostly in japanese roms (or just not removed for other countries) for compatibility with Famicombox device.<br /><a href="http://tripoint.org/kevtris/mappers/famicombox/index.html" class="postlink">http://tripoint.org/kevtris/mappers/famicombox/index.html</a><br />Device can check internal checksum and use internal name for its own purposes, but if you don't planned to export it to japan then don't mind. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=219">CaH4e3</a> — Fri Sep 15, 2006 1:03 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
